summary:
The Security Council,

Reaffirming previous resolutions and Presidential statements on Abyei and the Sudan-South Sudan border, 
Reaffirming commitment to Sudan and South Sudan's sovereignty, independence, unity, and territorial integrity, 
Noting steps to address insecurity in Abyei, and commending the Joint Political and Security Mechanism, 
Encouraging African Union mediation for temporary administrative and security arrangements in Abyei, 
Expressing concern over security threats to peacekeepers in UNISFA, 

1. Extends UNISFA's mandate until 15 November 2020, under Chapter VII, and tasks UNISFA to implement the mandate and tasks in accordance with resolution 2497 (2019);
2. Extends UNISFA's support to the Joint Border Verification and Monitoring Mechanism (JBVMM) until 15 November 2020, as a final extension unless parties take specific measures;
3. Maintains authorized troop and police ceilings, allowing postponement of troop withdrawal due to COVID-19;
4. Demands Sudan and South Sudan provide full support to UNISFA, including deployment of personnel and removal of obstacles;
5. Reiterates the Abyei area shall be demilitarized, except for UNISFA and the Abyei Police Service, and urges cooperation;
6. Requests the Secretary-General to report on progress in implementing UNISFA's mandate by 31 July and 15 October 2020;
7. Remains actively seized of the matter.
